Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.39,0:03:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure took your time, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.13,0:03:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to make up for\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}the deliveries I delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.63,0:03:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me your impressions of that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.26,0:03:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you speak to him too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:04:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You've had the closest\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}interaction with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.70,0:04:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing special?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He was all, "Whoa, what do I do?" like it was his first time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think he wanted to hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.90,0:04:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He did touch my butt a little, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.93,0:04:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in the Yunboro seemed\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}to understand what we were saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.84,0:04:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we ask him directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.72,0:04:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they get violent?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They destroyed the hangar in one hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.90,0:04:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You had a look at that Yunboroid, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.10,0:04:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and I have no idea how\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}it works or what it's made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.92,0:04:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't even stick a knife\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}between the joints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tough one, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.46,0:04:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Bellows?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.64,0:04:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice anything strange\Nwhen you retrieved it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I just pick up stuff that might be\N{\alpha&HFF&}..{\r}worth something, like I was told to—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That reminds me,\N the crane's broken now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.22,0:04:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No one told me that\N Yunboro would be so heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.87,0:04:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:04:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Not my fault\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}you're bad at your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Commodore{fleet commander} Fairlock, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.97,0:05:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.18,0:05:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that Yunboroid to be the\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}product of advanced technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.39,0:05:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should disassemble\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}and reverse engineer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.73,0:05:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.01,0:05:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That mech's nothing like the stuff we pulled up so far!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.49,0:05:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take it apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.19,0:05:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We can drag the pilot out and\N{\alpha&HFF&}..{\r}throw him into the sea with the boy—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.77,0:05:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They may not be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.33,0:05:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They could pose a\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}threat to the fleet later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you're getting at, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, what a spoilsport.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.47,0:05:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd best listen to the Commodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't risk facing their vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.50,0:05:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot identify any logic\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}behind your actions.{ep1}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain the reason why you\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}maintain this stalemate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My present armament is sufficient to resolve this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for the best at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My suggestion is as follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.57,0:05:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,One, overwhelm and\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}stifle their armed forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.13,0:06:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Two, suppress their leader\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}to prevent rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber, our top priority is to get in contact with our allies{i.e. the army allied with Ledo}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.97,0:06:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and identify our location.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.34,0:06:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Since your analysis has failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.34,0:06:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we're forced to rely on the\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}historical records of these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.45,0:06:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Conditionally agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.90,0:06:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important fact\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}is that the Earth is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.62,0:06:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought that the Sun's abnormal activity had turned it into a frozen wasteland,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,yet look around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.55,0:06:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.{ep1}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.96,0:06:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alliance has always been on the lookout for habitable planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.72,0:06:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This planet is rich in\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}both water and air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.31,0:06:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It could replace Avalon\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}as our new homeworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.10,0:06:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Remark: Your rank is not high enough to make that kind of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you manage to\Ncontact the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.13,0:06:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Distress signals were continuously sent, but there has been no response.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you persist with autonomous actions, you will run out of supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.11,0:07:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and that will impede your metabolism.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.01,0:07:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Suggestion number three.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.66,0:07:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You should consider withdrawing from this\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}situation and returning to artificial hibernation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.94,0:07:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.11,0:07:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.37,0:07:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's gonna fix my ship now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.34,0:07:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares, moron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.18,0:07:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.94,0:07:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.62,0:07:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How was the merman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Merman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard he took you hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.07,0:07:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How old is he?\N Is he handsome?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the whole fleet abuzz!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.80,0:07:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, just let me work!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.10,0:07:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the wings {\i1}before{\i0} you jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't skip the safety check!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.93,0:08:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rare piece of treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I'd let Ridget's crew nick it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.89,0:08:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a fine-toothed\N comb to that place!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.61,0:08:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Heya, Bevel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.24,0:08:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.17,0:08:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for running late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.97,0:08:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you were taken hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.06,0:08:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.51,0:08:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, he didn't mean any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.61,0:08:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's called Ledo, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.46,0:08:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say he's about as old as I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.45,0:08:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,His arms are really slim, \Nand he's kinda effeminate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.76,0:08:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another guy in his Yunboro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He talks weird, but at least he speaks our language.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.88,0:09:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can get along if we just keep talking to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.61,0:09:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you a present.{"gotcha a" looks weird}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.59,0:09:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.70,0:09:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.46,0:09:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My pleasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.96,0:09:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna talk with Ledo too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.66,0:09:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He might've come\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}from the sky, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.10,0:09:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky? Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.64,0:09:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know the stories{JOIN}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about the people who escaped to the stars when the planet froze?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.11,0:09:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:09:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a legend!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.82,0:10:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we found that\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}Yunboro under the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.60,0:10:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they've come from space.\N I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who escaped to space ages ago have come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Space, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.57,0:10:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd they bother\N coming all the way here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.31,0:10:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Ordum told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.71,0:10:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If ships could sail straight upwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.54,0:10:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we could make it to\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}space in just half a day!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.04,0:10:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.47,0:10:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{halftime}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she gonna be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.56,0:10:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Commodore was right to tell us not to\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}provoke{stimulate} them, but they can't stay there forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But why her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.50,0:11:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We had no other volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.61,0:11:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to go instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.67,0:11:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Conjecture: She poses little threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.34,0:11:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She might be an envoy sent for negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.93,0:11:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,An envoy? She's just a kid!{and what are you, mate}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.88,0:11:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I intercept?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.47,0:11:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.22,0:11:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the carcass of a marine creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.28,0:11:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A carcass?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.22,0:12:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What does she want?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.25,0:12:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It is presumed to be harmless food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.01,0:12:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants me to {\i1}eat{\i0} it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.41,0:12:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be deduced to be\N{\alpha&HFF&}.{\r}a ceremony of friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's a carcass!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.13,0:12:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber, inquire about her purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:26.43,runes,,0,0,0,,ik ek royto spulp
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.34,0:12:28.64,runes,,0,0,0,,haue kesma
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.40,0:12:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She requests dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.39,0:12:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.45,0:12:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He ate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.49,0:12:45.98,runes,,0,0,0,,hweh amy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.98,0:12:47.53,runes,,0,0,0,,osey dewo ekuek
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.30,0:12:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She calls herself Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.16,0:12:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She asks where you hail from.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.32,0:13:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.74,0:13:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're soldiers who\N fight the "Hideauze"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.29,0:13:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.41,0:13:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're stronger than those?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.93,0:13:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Super strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.97,0:13:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They're really from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess Bevel was right.
